entries.name: XCGLogger
entries.description: A debug log framework for use in Swift projects. Allows you to log details to the console (and optionally a file), just like you would have with NSLog or println, but with additional information, such as the date, function name, filename and line number.

entries.name: xcproj
entries.description: Swift library for reading and writing Xcode projects

entries.name: XcodeGen
entries.description: Generate your Xcode project from a spec file and your folder structure
